---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { withBase } from '../lib/paths';
---
<style>
.persona-hero { padding: 72px 0 64px; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
.persona-hero-ic { background: linear-gradient(160deg, #EFF6FF 0%, #DBEAFE 100%); }
.persona-hero h1 { color: var(--primary); font-size: clamp(28px, 3.5vw, 44px); font-weight: 900; letter-spacing: -0.03em; line-height: 1.1; margin-bottom: 16px; }
.persona-hero p { font-size: 18px; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 28px; }
.persona-nav {
  background: var(--white);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-100);
  position: sticky;
  top: 64px;
  z-index: 90;
}
.persona-nav-inner {
  max-width: 1160px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 24px;
  display: flex;
  gap: 4px;
  height: 52px;
  align-items: center;
}
.persona-nav-inner a {
  font-size: 14px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: var(--gray-500);
  text-decoration: none;
  padding: 6px 14px;
  border-radius: 7px;
  transition: background 0.15s, color 0.15s;
}
.persona-nav-inner a:hover { background: var(--gray-50); color: var(--primary); }
.use-case-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
  gap: 20px;
  margin-top: 40px;
}
.use-case-card { background: var(--white); border-radius: 14px; padding: 24px; border: 1px solid var(--gray-100); }
.use-case-card .icon { font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.use-case-card h4 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 8px; }
.use-case-card p { font-size: 13px; color: var(--gray-500); line-height: 1.6; }
.persona-section { padding: 80px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gray-100); }
.persona-section:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
.quote-block { background: var(--gray-50); border-radius: 14px; padding: 28px; border-left: 4px solid var(--secondary); margin: 32px 0; }
.quote-block p { font-size: 17px; font-style: italic; color: var(--gray-700); line-height: 1.65; margin-bottom: 12px; }
.quote-block .attribution { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--primary); }
.quote-block .role { font-size: 12px; color: var(--gray-500); margin-top: 2px; }
@media (max-width: 768px) { .use-case-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
</style>

<BaseLayout title="Solutions — Cadence for Every Layer of the Org" description="Cadence works for ICs who want visibility, managers who want to be better, senior leaders who need signal across their chain, CHROs who need operational command, and CEOs who need strategic altitude." activeNav="solutions">

<div class="page-hero">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="breadcrumb"><a href={withBase('/')}>Home</a><span>/</span>Solutions</div>
    <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(245,166,35,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(245,166,35,0.25);color:var(--accent-light);">Built for every layer</div>
    <h1>One platform. <span class="accent">Five perspectives.</span></h1>
    <p>Cadence looks different depending on where you sit: the IC sees clarity and coaching, the manager sees team health, the L2 sees signal across the chain, the CHRO sees operational command, and the CEO sees whether the org is healthy enough to execute.</p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="#individual-contributors" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Find your role ↓</a>
      <a href="https://app.cadencehr.ai/signup?intent=self-serve&source=apex-solutions" class="btn btn-white-outline btn-lg">Start free trial</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="persona-nav">
  <div class="persona-nav-inner">
    <a href="#individual-contributors">👤 Individual Contributors</a>
    <a href="#managers">🧑‍💼 Managers</a>
    <a href="#senior-leaders">📡 Senior Leaders</a>
    <a href="#chro">🏛️ CHROs</a>
    <a href="#ceo">📈 CEOs</a>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="persona-section" id="individual-contributors">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">Individual Contributors</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">Finally know where you stand — and where you're going.</h2>
        <p class="section-subhead" style="max-width:540px;margin-bottom:24px;">Management quality varies wildly across organizations. Some ICs get a manager who coaches them, advocates for them, and develops them deliberately. Most get someone who is too busy, too inconsistent, or too conflict-averse to be honest.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence doesn't fix your manager — it creates a system where good management happens by default, not by luck. Your 1:1s, goals, recognition history, role expectations, and private AI coaching live in one operating record.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"I spent 18 months at my last company not knowing if I was on track for a promotion or heading toward a PIP. Nobody told me. There was no system. Cadence changes that — everything is visible."</p>
          <div class="attribution">Software Engineer, L3</div>
          <div class="role">Beta program participant</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📋</div><h4>Your 1:1 record</h4><p>Every 1:1 you've ever had with your manager — documented, searchable, private.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🎯</div><h4>Your goals</h4><p>See your goals and status in the product. Goal context inside the 1:1 remains preview until tenant proof is attached.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">✦</div><h4>AI coaching</h4><p>Private coaching helps each participant prepare for better management conversations.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🏗️</div><h4>Job Architecture</h4><p>Role definitions, level context, and role assignments are live; growth paths inside the employee experience remain roadmap.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⭐</div><h4>Recognition</h4><p>Give and receive recognition tied to values. Your recognition history follows your tenure.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🗳️</div><h4>Your voice</h4><p>Pulse and engagement surveys designed for anonymous honesty.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="managers" style="background:var(--gray-50);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block reverse">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">Managers</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">The workspace you actually run your team in.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">Good management is hard. It requires you to be consistent, observant, coaching-oriented, and data-informed — all while doing your actual job. Most managers fail not because they don't care, but because they have no system.</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence is the system. Run your 1:1s here. Track your goals here. Use AI coaching in the management workflow. 9-box calibration and recognition-ratio enforcement remain preview until verified as GA.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"I've been a manager for six years. I thought I was good at it. The first month with Cadence showed me three relationships I was managing on autopilot that needed real attention."</p>
          <div class="attribution">VP Engineering</div>
          <div class="role">Beta program participant</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">💬</div><h4>1:1 workspace</h4><p>Structured agendas, shared with your direct report. Both parties contribute topics.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">✦</div><h4>Post-meeting AI coaching</h4><p>Private coaching helps managers improve without turning feedback into evaluation theater.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⬛</div><h4>9-box guidance roadmap</h4><p>Calibration guidance is planned, not part of current beta access.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⭐</div><h4>Recognition tracking preview</h4><p>Recognition posting is live; 5:1 ratio analysis is preview, not an enforced GA control.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🎯</div><h4>Team goals</h4><p>See direct-report goal status and progress. Goal surfacing inside 1:1s remains preview.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📊</div><h4>Team health signal</h4><p>Aggregate survey analytics are live; team-level attribution remains preview until verified.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="senior-leaders">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">Senior Leaders (L2+)</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">Complete signal across your entire management chain.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">Senior leaders are accountable for outcomes produced by people they don't directly manage. They need signal without micromanagement — the ability to see what's happening across their chain without having to ask or infer.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"I used to find out about management problems through resignations and complaints. Now I find out 90 days earlier, when the data starts showing the pattern."</p>
          <div class="attribution">Chief Product Officer</div>
          <div class="role">Beta program participant</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📡</div><h4>Chain-of-command preview</h4><p>Manager and org-health scorecards are live; full chain views and recognition ratios remain preview until tenant proof is attached.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⚠️</div><h4>Manager signal review</h4><p>Cadence helps leaders review manager activity across 1:1s, goals, recognition, and ER context without implying predictive attrition.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⬛</div><h4>Calibration participation roadmap</h4><p>Independent 9-box ratings and convergence views are roadmap previews for People-led calibration cycles.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🏆</div><h4>Top talent visibility roadmap</h4><p>Key Value Driver and retention-risk views are planned roadmap capabilities, not current beta access.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📊</div><h4>Survey signal aggregated</h4><p>Pulse responses and aggregate analytics are live; manager breakdowns remain preview.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📈</div><h4>Goal health across teams</h4><p>See the goal status for all teams in your chain. Identify blockers sitting unresolved.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="chro" style="background:var(--primary);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block" style="border-bottom:none;">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge" style="background:rgba(245,166,35,0.15);color:var(--accent-light);">CHROs &amp; People Leaders</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline white">Operational command — not just reporting.</h2>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">The CHRO's traditional view is backwards-looking: turnover reports, ER case counts, survey summaries published weeks after they're conducted. It tells you what happened, not what's happening.</p>
        <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.75);font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence gives the CHRO a management operating view across live 1:1, ER, recognition, survey, goal, and org-health signals. Calibration and predictive retention remain roadmap.</p>
        <div class="quote-block" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.06);border-left-color:var(--accent);">
          <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);">"The ROI conversation starts with replacing fragmented management workflows. Roadmap previews show where Cadence is going next."</p>
          <div class="attribution" style="color:white;">CHRO, Mid-market technology company</div>
          <div class="role" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.5);">Beta program participant · 850 employees</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">🏆</div><h4 style="color:white;">Culture Scorecard</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">Manager scorecard and org-health heatmap are live. Board-ready reporting remains preview.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">📋</div><h4 style="color:white;">ER pipeline</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">All active cases, PIPs, and formal investigations in one view.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">⬛</div><h4 style="color:white;">Calibration command roadmap</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">9-box cycle progress, KVD nominations, and predictive intervention workflows remain roadmap previews.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.07);border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.12);"><div class="icon">📉</div><h4 style="color:white;">Retention-risk roadmap</h4><p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.65);">Predictive retention warnings are planned, not currently available in production.</p></div>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align:center;margin-top:32px;">
          <a href="https://app.cadencehr.ai/signup?persona=chro&tier=professional&intent=trial&source=apex-solutions-chro" class="btn btn-accent btn-lg">Start a People team trial →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="persona-section" id="ceo" style="background:var(--gray-50);">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="feature-block reverse" style="border-bottom:none;">
      <div>
        <div class="section-badge">CEOs</div>
        <h2 class="section-headline">A strategic altitude view of whether the org is healthy.</h2>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:20px;">The CEO does not need another daily workflow. The CEO needs a fast answer to a harder question: is the organization healthy enough to execute?</p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--gray-500);line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">Cadence gives executives high-level Culture Scorecard metrics, manager-effectiveness hotspots, and focused drill-down when something catches attention. 9-box calibration visibility, predictive retention, and full KVD workflows remain roadmap until verified as live customer access.</p>
        <div class="quote-block">
          <p>"The CEO view should answer one question quickly: is the organization healthy enough to execute?"</p>
          <div class="attribution">Cadence product DNA</div>
          <div class="role">Executive view principle</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="use-case-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🏆</div><h4>Culture Scorecard rollup</h4><p>High-level org-health signal without forcing the CEO into every people workflow.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🔥</div><h4>Manager hotspots</h4><p>See where management quality needs attention before lagging outcomes become the only signal.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">⭐</div><h4>KVD roster roadmap</h4><p>Top-talent designation and movement are roadmap views, clearly separated from current live workflows.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">✅</div><h4>Intervention coverage</h4><p>Track whether bottom-left or at-risk situations have accountable follow-through.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">📈</div><h4>Org health trend lines</h4><p>Understand directionality across culture, goals, recognition, ER, and survey signals.</p></div>
          <div class="use-case-card"><div class="icon">🔎</div><h4>Targeted drill-down</h4><p>Move from board-level signal to the specific area that needs a leadership conversation.</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-cta">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Ready to see it in action?</h2>
    <p>Start a trial workspace or explore the platform by role before you bring Cadence to a broader leadership conversation.</p>
    <div class="btn-group" style="justify-content:center;">
      <a href="https://app.cadencehr.ai/signup?intent=self-serve&source=apex-solutions-cta" class="btn btn-white btn-lg">Start free trial</a>
      <a href={withBase('/product')} class="btn btn-white-outline btn-lg">Explore the platform</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
